The paper deals with a communication scenario involving encoding and decoding policies, which suggests that it may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of the Wiener process and real-time estimation suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of compression and sampling, which are topics commonly found in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the transmission of data over a channel, which suggests that it may also belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category.
